article.headline: Illinois State 54, Indianapolis 50
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Neil Plank scored 12 points Saturday to lead Illinois St. to a 54-50 win over Indianapolis in the season opener for both schools. Dana Ford added seven points, five rebounds and three steals, helping Illinois St. outscore Indianapolis 15-2 on fastbreaks. Daniel Cox led Indianapolis (0-1), scoring 10 points on 4-of-7 shooting, including two three-pointers. The Greyhounds led by seven points midway through the first half, but shot only 31 percent from the field in the game. Illinois State led 31-20 at the half.
